statement.title: Content
statement.content: Aftering learning the definition of the prime number, he is wondering how many prime numbers there are in $[n,m]$.So he wants you to help to solve this problem.

statement.title: Standard Input
statement.content: There are several test cases.For each test case, standard input contains a line with two numbers $n$ and $m$ ($1\leq n\leq m\leq 10^9$). The input ends with $n = m = 0$.

statement.title: Standard Output
statement.content: For each test case, print the answer.

statement.title: Samples
statement.content:
Input Output
1 6 4 12 0 03 3
